[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with murder after Mintlaw takeaway death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court charged with murder after the death of a man at a takeaway in Aberdeenshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Shahzad Shah, 56, died following an incident at Mirchi Indian takeaway in Mintlaw on Monday.
Hidayet Ozden, 52, of Falkirk, appeared at Peterhead Sheriff Court charged with murder and assault.
He made no plea or declaration and was remanded in custody. He is expected to appear again on 21 April.
